		<div class="post" id="">
		    <div class="title"><h1><a href="/ldap/">LDAP</a></h1></div>
		    <p>LDAP, is the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lightweight_Directory_Access_Protocol">Lightweight Directory Access Protocol</a>, a protocol for accessing and
maintaining directory services. I've done quite a bit with LDAP, and here are some
select postings:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2007/06/22/editing-ldap-with-vi/">Editing LDAP with vi</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/pages/ldap-external/">LDAP EXTERNAL mechanism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2006/03/02/ssh-public-keys-from-ldap/">SSH Public Keys from LDAP</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2006/05/24/exims-smarthost-from-ldap/">Exim's SmartHost from LDAP</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2011/08/09/extending-unbound-with-python-module/">Extending the Unbound DNS server with Python</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2006/05/30/using-sasls-external-mechanism-from-perl/">Using SASL's EXTERNAL mechanism from Perl</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2009/11/17/exim-expands-ldap-posixgroup/">Exim expands LDAP posixGroup</a></li>
<li><a href="http://jpmens.net/2006/01/02/sexy-exim/">sexy Exim: LDAP in Exim</a></li>
</ul>



	
		

